47
00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:48.040
A minimum of one camera per nested level sequence is needed, whether it's spawnable or possessible.

48
00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:53.360
And most importantly, you'll need a camera cuts track to generate footage.

49
00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:58.760
When played in sequence, the parent level sequence pulls camera binding data from each

50
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:03.520
shot's camera cuts track so it knows which camera it's looking through and what needs

51
00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:04.520
to be rendered.

52
00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:09.680
The result is a continuous sequence when played back through the timeline.

53
00:04:09.680 --> 00:04:14.439
As impressive as nested level sequences are, you might not need so much complexity.

